The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for image super-resolution in MRI, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel 3D CNN architecture and uses generative adversarial network (GAN) for training, which are popular techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a large public dataset, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
